chunk_content: Where can data for this indicator be found? Data on engagement in CQI and PT can be obtained from program records of PEPFAR- funded partners. Additionally, laboratory-based testing and POCT site-level documentation can be used to assess CQI and PT engagement. Data on the number of specimens received for testing can be obtained from specimen registers/logbooks and/or laboratory information systems (L. How are data interpreted and reported (Laboratory-Based Testing)? Identify the level of engagement in CQI activities for each laboratory-based testing site by choosing one of the following: • Performs this test but does not participate in CQI (see definition of “CQI participation” below). • Performs this test, participates in CQI, but is not fully accredited (see definition of “accreditation” below). • Performs this test, participates in CQI, and is fully accredited.
